Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.20,0:00:09.44,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The troublesome Croce di Pietro, it turns out, can be used regardless of place or season.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.06,0:00:15.11,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, Academy City will fall under control of the Roman Catholics by sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.82,0:00:18.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way I'm letting that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.69,0:02:08.12,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, your head is in quite a convenient position.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.52,0:02:18.82,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.27,0:02:31.98,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The sky's getting dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.07,0:02:36.42,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, isn't it time for you to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.86,0:02:41.56,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you want to experience a stimulating night with this Onee-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.32,0:02:44.45,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Just one more...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.57,0:02:50.55,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,One more thing... Something to get an advantage...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.55,0:02:51.77,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,One more...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.30,0:03:06.30,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire is thy name,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.30,0:03:08.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,bearing the title of sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.36,0:03:12.11,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Show yourself. Devour my body and transform into power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.82,0:03:14.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Innocentius!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.17,0:03:28.32,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Innocentius.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.75,0:03:30.42,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortis931...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.05,0:03:36.51,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll prove why my name is called the strongest here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:39.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Die together!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:42.86,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's dangerous, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.47,0:03:46.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no{\fscx250}-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.15,0:03:50.59,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ashes to ashes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.59,0:03:51.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Dust to dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.87,0:03:54.50,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Vampire Hunter Crimson Cross!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.21,0:04:00.45,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back home, you useless magician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.45,0:04:01.93,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, amateur!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.58,0:04:11.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Innocentius!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.48,0:04:17.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in the way, idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.79,0:04:18.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, move aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.99,0:04:20.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What is happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:22.54,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't read their movements...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:37.00,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,A basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.80,0:04:40.18,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want an absolute basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.51,0:04:43.21,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,A clear rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.83,0:04:45.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So that everyone will be happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.99,0:04:50.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and so everyone can avoid conflict arising due to differing values.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.27,0:04:52.48,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I want that wonderful world...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.71,0:04:55.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I must win.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.70,0:04:57.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll win and create an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.96,0:05:00.63,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,My name...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.63,0:05:03.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Basis104.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:05.57,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Get down, amateur!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.27,0:05:17.28,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.33,0:05:18.88,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.95,0:05:22.26,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, your opponent is me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.60,0:05:27.31,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop messing around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.31,0:05:29.36,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,How many people must you hurt before you're satisfied?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.00,0:05:33.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This Onee-san doesn't want to hurt anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.25,0:05:36.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have a purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.21,0:05:38.96,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So come!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.20,0:05:43.22,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I crush you, boy, this Onee-san's mission will be complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.22,0:05:49.84,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Croce di Pietro and the Roman Catholics will create the world I desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.43,0:05:52.36,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.36,0:05:57.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't speak so arrogantly while letting others decide your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.83,0:06:00.13,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Letting others decide...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.63,0:06:04.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, this Onee-san doesn't really care who's in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:09.82,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as they dominate and standardize the ideals and principles of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.37,0:06:14.31,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,this Onee-san will defend that basis to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:17.73,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your goal?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.25,0:06:21.31,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really understand such difficult and confusing topics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.31,0:06:27.91,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't accept something stupid like handing over everyone in Academy City for that goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.34,0:06:32.44,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, you say those things because you don't know anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.28,0:06:37.37,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone just standing dumbfounded, helpless against their situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.37,0:06:39.79,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,because you've never seen that expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.52,0:06:44.02,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you've never watched someone moan "it hurts" while suffering in anguish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.57,0:06:49.72,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, that's no excuse for attacking Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.06,0:06:55.55,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's never a reason to use someone as a stepping stone for someone else's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.09,0:06:57.83,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.05,0:07:05.83,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Your problems are something that everyone else feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.42,0:07:09.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone deals with failure, and sometimes they fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.71,0:07:11.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.10,0:07:12.76,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you fall, then just stand back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.08,0:07:16.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the result is miserable... Even if it doesn't go as planned,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.10,0:07:17.54,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,keep standing back up!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.54,0:07:20.95,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You have no right to use other people's lives as you please!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.09,0:07:24.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Which one will you choose, Oriana Thomson?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.68,0:07:29.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you leave everything to someone else because you failed once?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.94,0:07:35.68,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Or will you take that failure, and lend a hand towards those who make the same mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.60,0:07:44.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,With this, everything will end.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.75,0:07:50.41,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I call on all the talent that dwells within me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:54.32,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,release everything, and destroy the enemy ahead!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.20,0:08:22.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.13,0:08:25.60,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.60,0:08:28.96,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you put any effort towards making this event a success?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:31.69,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a bit of a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.49,0:08:33.01,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.66,0:08:36.91,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't expect too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:38.84,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not my specialty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:41.41,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Kami-yan.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.86,0:08:43.12,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:45.96,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all trying to protect the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.31,0:08:49.33,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be at your hospital room before the Night Parade starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.75,0:08:51.46,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,So please, wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:55.30,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,I accepted their determination with mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.58,0:09:02.40,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let it go waste, not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.35,0:09:29.37,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stiyl!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.81,0:09:31.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.81,0:09:33.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, find the Croce di Pietro.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.05,0:09:37.56,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Force Oriana to tell where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.33,0:09:41.26,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that thing from activating.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.79,0:09:44.05,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:45.71,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything will be over soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.96,0:09:48.81,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Lidvia Lorenzetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.46,0:09:55.07,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shortly, the Croce di Pietro will activate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:10:00.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Academy City will be placed under control of the Roman Catholics.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:04.58,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So you plan to get rid of us meddlers here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.09,0:10:10.46,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We feel your pain and wish to heal your wounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.74,0:10:15.25,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, only if we judge it to be beneficial for the Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.58,0:10:16.67,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.67,0:10:19.57,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to reason with her, Kamijou Touma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.41,0:10:24.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lidvia must be somewhere near by, the spiritual tool should be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.03,0:10:27.40,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,To avoid any misunderstandings, let me tell you this,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.40,0:10:31.11,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Croce di Pietro is not in Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.41,0:10:32.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.83,0:10:37.56,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Roman Catholic Church, which was created by the Croce di Pietro,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.56,0:10:41.31,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,at its peak occupied 47,000 square kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.31,0:10:46.24,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's activated from outside, it will completely cover Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.30,0:10:48.67,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We were tricked...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.67,0:10:49.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oriana was just a decoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:10:54.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfortunate that she was beaten.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.17,0:10:59.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Croce di Pietro will change the situation to make that beneficial to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.70,0:11:04.02,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's important now is that science will bow to religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:10.72,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,By denying science of what they believe, we will restore the power of our Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:13.85,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Searching and attacking,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.43,0:11:17.98,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,it's impossible for Tsuchimikado to use magic twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:19.46,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:21.00,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.44,0:11:25.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We will not destroy Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.03,0:11:30.89,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you forsake science, we will accept you as our fellow comrades.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.56,0:11:30.89,Index II main overlap,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Call Tsuchimikado.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.62,0:11:34.95,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Have him use the Senjutsu Enjin to calculate Lidvia's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.95,0:11:38.83,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll use my communication spell to call my allies outside to take care of it{\fscx250}-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.29,0:11:40.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.98,0:11:44.09,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The time left for Croce di Pietro to change the world is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.29,0:11:47.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,107 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.73,0:11:49.02,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.74,0:11:52.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there nothing else?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.40,0:11:55.98,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there an ultimate trump card that can reverse this situation?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.86,0:11:59.95,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,A spell used by the constellations in the night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.95,0:12:02.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Gathering starlight on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.33,0:12:09.37,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsuchimikado!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.68,0:12:15.42,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,How many places outside Academy City can they use the Croce di Pietro and still cover Academy City?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.79,0:12:16.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.90,0:12:18.25,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:21.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Among those conditions, which is the furthest point?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.51,0:12:23.57,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The northern perimeter of Academy City.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.57,0:12:25.84,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,About 1700 meters away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.84,0:12:27.47,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.22,0:12:36.40,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Just...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:37.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,20 more seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.45,0:12:45.09,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.06,0:12:51.96,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, it's the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.85,0:12:56.13,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is the end, then it's over for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.82,0:13:01.42,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so too, Lidvia?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.02,0:13:04.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I've destroyed your illusion,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.16,0:13:07.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't keep the promise I made with my classmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.93,0:13:10.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.37,0:13:32.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The time is exactly 6:30 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.07,0:13:34.45,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.73,0:13:39.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the time when the Night Parade starts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.17,0:13:42.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,With this amount of light, all the stars will be hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.43,0:13:46.38,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.26,0:13:54.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You lost to the light that everyone released to defend the Daihaseisai.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.45,0:14:00.15,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have checked out who the main character of the Daihaseisai was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.71,0:14:01.89,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.89,0:14:04.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you let me destroy the Croce di Pietro,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.57,0:14:08.67,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and promise not to do anything else to Academy City,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.41,0:14:11.18,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,then I'll be fine leaving you alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.45,0:14:13.33,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you serious saying that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.33,0:14:17.28,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to have forgotten that I'm a devout member of the Roman Catholic Church.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.63,0:14:19.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.98,0:14:30.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, you should get to running around just like in a sports festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.10,0:14:31.76,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lidvia Lorenzetti.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.72,0:14:42.53,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.53,0:14:45.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma didn't say anything to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.10,0:14:49.31,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and ran off to fight a magical battle that involved the fate of the world and Academy City,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.31,0:14:52.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and got so badly wounded that he was sent back to the hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:54.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Index-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.70,0:14:58.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,whenever I mention a magical incident you thoughtlessly walk right into the middle of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.25,0:15:03.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Touma, your explanation seems to imply that I'm an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.84,0:15:08.34,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you haven't realized that yourself, then you must really{\fscx250}-
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.65,0:15:11.98,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.18,0:15:15.27,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is truly a pleasant scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.20,0:15:19.99,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,We're having a serious discussion, so don't interfere, Short-Hair!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:23.94,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroko...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.67,0:15:30.32,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ordinary civilians are allowed to help Judgment in maintaining discipline, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.90,0:15:33.00,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Onee-sama,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.00,0:15:35.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,that's going too far, this is a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.99,0:15:36.95,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.40,0:15:38.47,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.76,0:15:40.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen today's final results?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:45.34,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Our school has comfortably surpassed yours and is in the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.34,0:15:48.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't forgotten about the penalty game, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.14,0:15:52.57,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, putting aside the penalty game, I can't even participate in matches like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.89,0:15:54.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.40,0:15:56.82,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Be prepared to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:09.17,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,How pitiful, Oriana Thompson.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.41,0:16:11.97,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.16,0:16:15.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I must save, with my own hands, that lost sinner who was arrested{\fscx250}-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.80,0:16:18.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, ah, attention please!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.73,0:16:24.30,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Archbishop of the Anglican Church, Laura Stuart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.30,0:16:29.64,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I've introduced myself, why don't you stop being so cold, Miss Lidvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.89,0:16:32.70,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,How did you find this private jet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.41,0:16:39.43,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I arranged for a little present to be stuck on the outside of your plane when you stopped at Haneda.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.34,0:16:42.62,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're as creepy as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:47.81,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That personality of yours makes you laugh louder the more pressure you're put under.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.12,0:16:50.16,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't that behavior be corrected?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.38,0:16:54.84,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The more difficult the situation is, the greater the joy will be in overcoming it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.55,0:16:58.32,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I must give thanks to the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.16,0:17:04.18,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.63,0:17:11.21,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The greater the wall, the more joy will be had in surpassing it, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:16.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,There is indeed some sense in those words,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.32,0:17:18.14,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,when spoken by an animal trapped against the cliff's edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.07,0:17:41.09,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Lidvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.09,0:17:46.40,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,If you give up on Rome's teachings and lick my feet, I'll save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:48.41,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What nonsense do you speak?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.51,0:17:49.22,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.77,0:17:52.88,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Then fall with that thing and make a crater in the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.31,0:17:56.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Croce di Pietro?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.67,0:17:59.24,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't allow that to happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.06,0:18:03.19,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Calculating the descent speed, I should make it{\fscx250}-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.19,0:18:06.01,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I have to make it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.21,0:18:07.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Time is short...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.78,0:18:09.04,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's what makes it so fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.70,0:18:17.07,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So Lidvia, which will you choose?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.39,0:18:19.63,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The greatest spiritual tool in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.63,0:18:21.87,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,or a poor lost lamb?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.58,0:18:36.33,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,When the obstacle ahead is even bigger, when you overcome it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.33,0:18:41.51,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll have an even greater joy trampling over me, who created the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.56,0:18:43.72,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Trample?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.07,0:18:49.48,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Over that unreachable flower, as much as I want...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.05,0:19:11.73,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That was quite a tremor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.66,0:19:17.19,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The development of Imagine Breaker, the key, is still unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.13,0:19:21.13,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I can use this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.31,0:19:28.56,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I may have to consider the possibility that I'd have to take action personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.06,0:19:44.12,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.65,0:19:47.39,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I was sleeping on the bench in the waiting room,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.72,0:19:51.20,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but they told me I can't use it after it's morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.20,0:19:53.72,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Such a soft bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.44,0:19:57.10,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.59,0:20:02.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Frog-faced doctor said I'll be discharged tomorrow or the day after.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.08,0:20:07.35,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Aisa, you look somewhat lonely.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.70,0:20:08.51,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Why's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.34,0:20:15.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy, did he do something reckless again?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.53,0:20:17.16,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.64,0:20:21.39,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen here, I haven't heard the details yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.39,0:20:27.52,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems some Roman Catholic magicians took advantage of the Daihaseisai to attack us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.06,0:20:33.05,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, Touma didn't bother to tell me anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.05,0:20:37.25,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,and rushed headlong into the battle, and only reported it to me after everything was over.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.85,0:20:39.06,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unforgivable, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.84,0:20:42.04,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.39,0:20:44.23,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter who's involved...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.66,0:20:48.43,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,That person will save anyone in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.43,0:20:50.12,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.05,0:20:56.22,Index II main I,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I shouldn't have been saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.37,0:21:00.48,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to only bring trouble to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.63,0:21:03.29,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.69,0:21:11.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Because, Touma and Aisa seem to be happy together.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.70,0:21:17.95,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Say Fukiyose-san, how can you come all the way to the hospital just to slap a patient?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.95,0:21:18.80,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.82,0:21:22.50,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone would be shocked to see a naked boy all of a sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.50,0:21:24.90,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who barged in when I was changing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.90,0:21:25.65,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.65,0:21:30.24,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you know why that person continues to fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.60,0:21:31.23,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.79,0:21:35.12,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked him, he said it was for his own sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.83,0:21:39.00,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe to Touma, that's what happiness means.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.37,0:23:28.54,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Luckily or unluckily, Index and I suddenly won a trip to Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.74,0:23:30.83,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Since that's the case, we ought to enjoy ourselves to the fullest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.91,0:23:32.78,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Orsola?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.78,0:23:34.05,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,The Amakusa too?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.49,0:23:36.03,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode: "The Metropolis of Water."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.25,0:23:39.49,Index II main,,0000,0000,0000,,When science and magic cross paths, the story begins.
